Mattel Told to Pay MGA $85 Million Punitive Damages in Bratz Doll Dispute

-- B y   E d v a r d   P e t t e r s s o n
-- 
2011-08-04T21:58:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/mattel-told-to-pay-mga-85-million-punitive-damages-in-bratz-doll-dispute.html
Mattel Inc. (MAT) , the world biggest
toymaker, must pay MGA Entertainment Inc., maker of Bratz dolls,
$85 million in punitive damages, as well as $2.5 million in
attorney fees and costs, a judge said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edvard Pettersson in Los Angeles at 
 epettersson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Blumberg at 
